{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox artist | bgcolour = #6495ED | name = Thomas (Tomas) Furlong | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth-date|df=yes|28 February 1886}} | birth_place = [[St.Louis]], [[Missouri]] | death_date = {{death-date|1952}} | death_place = [[Bolton Landing, New York]] | nationality = [[Scotch-Irish Americans|Scotch-Irish American]] | field = Painting, [[muralist]] | training = [[Art Students League]] | movement = [[Modern art]], [[Realism (arts)|realism]], [[impressionism]] | works = | patrons = [[Oliver Gould Jennings]] [[Hyde Collection]], [[Bolton Museum]], [[Weber Furlong Foundation]], [[Building 98|Studio 98]], | influenced by = [[Paul Cézanne]], [[Henri Matisse]], [[Edmund H. Wuerpel]], [[Wilhelmina Weber Furlong]] | influenced = [[David Smith (sculptor)|David Smith]], [[Jackson Pollock]], [[Willem de Kooning]], [[Dorothy Dehner]], [[Jean Charlot|Jean Charolot]], [[Alexander Calder]], [[Rockwell Kent]], [[Kimon Nicolaïdes]], [[Max Weber (artist)]] , [[Allen Tucker]], [[John D. Graham|John Graham]], [[Thomas Hart Benton (painter)|Thomas Hart Benton]], [[Wilhelmina Weber Furlong]] | awards = }}
'''Thomas (Tomas) Furlong''' (1886–1952) was a [[Scotch-Irish Americans|Scotch-Irish American]] artist and teacher.<ref name="TheBiography">The Biography of Wilhelmina Weber Furlong: The Treasured Collection of Golden Heart Farm by Clint Bernard Weber, {{ISBN|978-0-9851601-0-4}}</ref><ref>Professor Emeritus James K. Kettlewell: Harvard,Skidmore College,Curator The Hyde Collection. Foreword to The Treasured Collection of Golden Heart Farm. {{ISBN|978-0-9851601-0-4}}</ref>
==Biography== Furlong was a member of the executive Board of Control of the Art Students League and beginning in 1927 an art instructor at [[New York University]]. He was married to [[Wilhelmina Weber Furlong]]. In the American modern art movement, his significant circle of friends and acquaintances included [[John D. Graham|John Graham]],<ref name="SmithsonianArchives">Smithsonian Archives of American Art Oral history interviews with Dorothy Dehner, 1965 Oct. – 1966</ref> [[Willem de Kooning|Wilem de Kooning]], [[David Smith (sculptor)|David Smith]],<ref name="SmithsonianArchives" /> [[Dorothy Dehner]],<ref name="SmithsonianArchives" /> [[Jean Charlot|Jean Charolot]], [[Alexander Calder]], [[Rockwell Kent|Rockwell and Sally Kent]], [[Thomas Hart Benton (painter)|Thomas Hart Benton]], [[Allen Tucker]], [[Max Weber (artist)|Max Weber]], [[Kimon Nicolaïdes|Kimon Nicolaidies]], and many others.<ref>Smithsonian Archives of American Art Detailed description of the Ben Benn papers, 1905–1993</ref> Thomas Furlong lived and worked in New York, City and shared a gallery with his wife Wilhelmina Weber Furlong. He was a [[Realism (arts)|realist]] and an accomplished [[muralist]].<ref name="TheBiography"/>
